abstract = { Abstract The recently developed orbital-free embedding scheme based on partitioning of the electron density (Kohn-Sham equations wit constrained electron density, KSCED) is applied to determine the hyperfine interaction tensor for charge-transfer complexes of the MCO2 type (M=Li, Na, or K). In the applied approach, CO2 is considered as one subsystem for which the spin-density is obtained using Kohn-Sham-like one-electron effective potential. The KSCED effective embedding potential is expressed using explicit functionals of the electron densities of the considered subsystems. It comprises the terms of known analytic form and the components which are approximated (the exchange-correlation potential and non-additive kinetic energy potential). It is shown that the current implementation of KSCED is applicable to such complexes for which the distribution of the total charge among the interacting subsystems is known. For LiCO2 and NaCO2 which are treated as \${\rm Li}^{+}{\rm CO}^{-}\_{2}\$ and \${\rm Na}^{+}{\rm CO}^{-}\_{2}\$ in KSCED, the KSCED results, the supermolecule Kohn-Sham ones, and the available experimental data are in a very good agreement.}
